<tr valign="top" height="400" >
<td tEditID="c1r1" style=" background-color:#FFFFFF; bEditID:r3st1; color:#000000; bLabel:main; font-size:12pt; font-family:arial;" aEditID="c1r1" locked="0" >
<![CDATA[<div style=""><div style=""><div style=""><div style=""><div style=""><div style=""><div style=""><div style=""><div style=""><p class="MsoNormal" style=""><span style="font-family: Arial, sans-serif; line-height: 17.12px; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;"><span style="background-color: white;">Hi {!Contact.FirstName},<br></span><br>Thank you for getting in touch with Kingsbridge.<br></span><span style="font-family: Arial, sans-serif;"><br><b>Professional Indemnity Insurance<br></b></span><span style="font-family: Arial, sans-serif;">Professional Indemnity insurance is designed to protect businesses against claims for negligence (such as making a mistake or giving inaccurate advice).<br></span><span style="font-family: Arial, sans-serif;"><br><b>Claims made basis<br></b></span><span style="font-family: Arial, sans-serif;">Professional Indemnity insurance operates on a 'claims made' basis, so the policy can only respond to claims notified during the policy period.&nbsp;<br></span><span style="font-family: Arial, sans-serif;"><br>For this reason, holding a live Professional Indemnity policy even when not working is essential to safeguard against potential claims for previous work completed.&nbsp;<br></span><span style="font-family: Arial, sans-serif;"><br>Because Professional Indemnity insurance operates on a ‘claims made’ basis, you must notify us of a claim during the Period of Insurance (as per our&nbsp;<a href="https://www.kingsbridge.co.uk/policy-documents/">Policy Wording</a>).<br></span><br style="font-family: Arial, sans-serif;"><b style="font-family: Arial, sans-serif;">Financial Conduct Authority&nbsp;</b><b style="font-family: Arial, sans-serif;"><br></b><a href="https://www.fca.org.uk/firms/regdata/rma-e-professional-indemnity-insurance-self" style="font-family: Arial, sans-serif; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);">The Financial Conduct Authority</a><span style="font-family: Arial, sans-serif;">&nbsp;describes this as follows, “</span><i style="font-family: Arial, sans-serif;">Professional Indemnity insurance policies work on a ‘claims made’ basis, which means the current Professional Indemnity insurance insurer is the one responsible for meeting any claims made on a policy, even when claims pre-date that policy</i><span style="font-family: Arial, sans-serif;">.”<br></span><br style="font-family: Arial, sans-serif;"><b style="font-family: Arial, sans-serif;">Retroactive cover<br></b><span style="font-family: Arial, sans-serif;">Kingsbridge offer full ‘retroactive cover’ on many of our package policies. This is to cover any previous claims that may arise during the period of insurance - however, once the policy expires or is cancelled, no cover is in place. So, if any claim is made against you after cancellation, it won’t be covered under this policy.</span><br style="font-family: Arial, sans-serif;"><br style="font-family: Arial, sans-serif;"><span style="font-family: Arial, sans-serif;">Hopefully this information clearly demonstrates that we’re following FCA guidelines within our policy, but please don’t hesitate to reply to this email if you need any further information on any of the above.</span><br style="font-family: Arial, sans-serif;"><br style="font-family: Arial, sans-serif;"><span style="font-family: Arial, sans-serif; background-color: white;">Kind regards,</span><span style="font-family: Arial, sans-serif; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);"><br></span><span style="font-family: Arial, sans-serif; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);"><br></span><span style="font-family: Arial, sans-serif;">{!User.FirstName}</span><br style="font-family: Arial, sans-serif;"><span style="font-family: Arial, sans-serif;">Customer Service Team</span><br style="font-family: Arial, sans-serif;"><br style="font-family: Arial, sans-serif;"><span style="font-family: Arial, sans-serif;">E: customersupport@kingsbridge.co.uk</span><br style="font-family: Arial, sans-serif;"><span style="font-family: Arial, sans-serif;">T: 01242 808 740</span></p></div></div></div></div></div></div></div></div></div>]]></td>
</tr>
</table>